The paper deals with unsupervised object modeling and localization in robotics using RGB-D images. This involves computer vision (CV) techniques such as keypoint extraction, matching, and clustering, as well as robotics (RO) applications such as object picking with a robotic arm. The method also utilizes geometric criteria and clustering, which are common in artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (LG) research. Finally, the paper presents results on various objects, which could fall under graphics (GR) or computer vision (CV) sub-categories. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, and cs.GR.
